Author::::Chemist85
DateTime::::2016-03-06T06:35:41Z
1. Don't drink too much in the morning. 2. Caffiene is your friend, use it wisely. 3. Take electrolyte tabs with you. 4. Plan when you refuel, it helps split the race into smaller sections. 5. Peanut butter and jam butties cut into bitesize cubes, frozen overnight. Perfect at mile 18 when you hit the wall.6. Ibuprofen to have with the butties at mile 18. Lifesaver.7. Use the pace runners. A good pace runner will keep the group around then engaged while keeping a set pace.8. For the love of god, do not eat the jelly babies that kids hand out. Think of all those sweaty penis hands that have been in that tub before yours. 9. There's no shame in talking to yourself at mile 20 and beyond.



