Author::::alldoomed
DateTime::::2016-03-04T11:21:56Z
12 marathons PB 3hrs 1m (yes, I know it's a bummer). Training is the key: build up to a weekly mileage of 50-55 with at least a 20 miler a week before the race. Three beers a week. Taper down training with two non-running days before the race. Drink water only during the race. Wear hat if it's sunny. Work out your anticipated average minutes per mile and try to stick with it. Don't start off too fast. Obviously wear decent shoes that have been totally run-in.Trust me.



