Do the training, and don't skip the long runs. Get to the start line fit and healthy, with adequate nutrition and hydration. Have a race plan and stick to it. Be conservative. First time is for getting around,, next time you can push harder. Better to finish and think you could have run faster than die at 20 miles because you pushed too fast too early.



